  <bioghist id="aspace_65fc6f5f1958dff10457a87fb02785a4">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>The President's Council of Cornell Women (PCCW) was founded in 1990 by former President Frank Rhodes. It is a group of alumnae working to enhance the involvement of women students, faculty, staff, and alumnae as leaders within Cornell University and its many communities.</p>  </bioghist>
  <prefercite id="aspace_89a689ca35d5eed42b66881367669fdb">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>President's Council of Cornell Women Records, #41-9-3922. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_35c9b30a01caed68281b63e422a1f1da">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>Includes meeting minutes, bylaws, membership information, publicity photographs, DVDs, CDs and videotapes.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <scopecontent audience="internal" id="aspace_cf7e1e481be1cd873c663f4179f0f590">
    <head>Scope and content</head>
<p>PCCW Fall meeting material, 2014; PCCW Annual Meeting At-A-Glance program, 2014; 25th Anniversary Annual Meeting 2015 meeting packet, infographic poster signed by meeting attendees, and letter of congratulations from President David J. Skorton.</p>  </scopecontent>
